revision.text: ==English== ===Etymology=== From {{suffix|en|yearn|some}}. ===Adjective=== {{en-adj}} # Expressing, indicating, or full of [[yearning]]; [[yearnful]]; [[desirous]]. #* '''1919''', ''Winter Sports Verse'': #*: And ah! a '''yearnsome''' sigh / Escapes from scores of swains, who far and nigh / To win the slightest notice vainly try, {{...}} #* '''1990''', Pete Davies, ''Dollarville'': #*: He'd been on Mir for six months, and was kind of '''yearnsome''' for new company. #* '''2005''', Paul Seaton, ''Cats Don't Eat Pancakes'': #*: I'm in complete control, my '''yearnsome''' drones.
